name: S-ribosylhomocysteine lyase
classes: Carbon-sulfur lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
comment: Contains Fe2+. The 4,5-dihydroxypentan-2,3-dione formed spontaneously cyclizes and combines with borate to form an autoinducer (AI-2) in the bacterial quorum-sensing mechanism, which is used by many bacteria to control gene expression in response to cell density [2].

references.title: S-Ribosylhomocysteinase (LuxS) is a mononuclear iron protein.
